  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Baseline: 0% coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no test files anywhere in the repo, and `pytest`/`pytest-asyncio` aren't even in `requirements.txt`. Every one of the 7 source modules (`models.py`, `filters.py`, `pipeline.py`, `store.py`, `notify.py`, `cli.py`, `agent.py`) and all 15 ATS parsers in `fetchers.py` are completely untested.\n\n### Suggested setup (one-time)\n```\nrequirements-dev.txt: pytest, pytest-asyncio, respx (httpx mocking), freezegun (or monkeypatch time)\ntests/\n  conftest.py        # tmp Store fixture, sample Job factory\n  test_models.py\n  test_filters.py\n  test_store.py\n  test_fetchers.py\n  test_pipeline.py\n  test_notify.py\n  test_agent.py\n  test_cli.py\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — untested entirely\n\n`parse_posted_at` has three branches (epoch-ms, epoch-s, ISO-8601, prose-failure) and none are tested.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected_epoch_s\", [\n    (\"1643241332430\", 1643241332),   # Lever ms epoch\n    (\"1643241332\", 1643241332),      # plain seconds epoch\n    (\"-5\", -5),                      # negative numeric edge case\n])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_numeric(value, expected_epoch_s):\n    dt = parse_posted_at(value)\n    assert dt.timestamp() == expected_epoch_s\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_iso_with_z():\n    dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n    assert dt == datetime(2024, 1, 15, 10, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\ndef test_parse_posted_at_iso_naive_assumes_utc():\n    dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n    assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value\", [\"\", None, \"Posted 3 Days Ago\", \"not-a-date\"])\ndef test_parse_posted_at_unparseable_returns_none(value):\n    assert parse_posted_at(value) is None\n\ndef test_job_key_is_stable_identity():\n    j = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"123\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n    assert j.key == \"lever:acme:123\"\n\ndef test_job_content_hash_changes_on_title_but_not_on_id():\n    base = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\", location=\"NY\")\n    same_id_diff_title = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Sr Eng\", url=\"u\", location=\"NY\")\n    diff_id_same_fields = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"2\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\", location=\"NY\")\n    assert base.content_hash != same_id_diff_title.content_hash\n    assert base.content_hash == diff_id_same_fields.content_hash  # hash excludes external_id\n\ndef test_job_to_row_excludes_raw_and_adds_key_and_hash():\n    j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"t\", url=\"u\", raw={\"x\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row\n    assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n    assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py` — untested entirely\n\nWord-boundary regex matching, exclude-before-include precedence, and the cutoff's \"keep unparseable dates\" behavior are all subtle and unverified.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    defaults = dict(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Backend Engineer\",\n                     url=\"u\", location=\"Remote - US\", department=\"Engineering\")\n    return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n\ndef test_include_keyword_word_boundary_no_substring_match():\n    # \"eng\" should not match \"Engineering\" as a substring per word-boundary regex\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Engineering Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is True  # \\bENG\\b in \"Engineering\"? verify boundary behavior\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Design\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n\ndef test_exclude_takes_precedence_over_include():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Backend Engineer (Intern)\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"engineer\"], exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\ndef test_locations_case_insensitive_substring():\n    assert match(_job(location=\"San Francisco, CA\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is True\n    assert match(_job(location=\"Remote\"), locations=[\"san francisco\"]) is False\n\ndef test_locations_empty_list_job_location_matches_nothing():\n    assert match(_job(location=\"\"), locations=[\"nyc\"]) is False\n\ndef test_cutoff_drops_old_confirmed_date():\n    old = _job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n    assert match(old, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)) is False\n\ndef test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at():\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # Workday prose, currently unparsed\n    assert match(j, cutoff=datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)) is True\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_builds_cutoff(monkeypatch):\n    fresh = _job(external_id=\"1\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    stale = _job(external_id=\"2\", posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat())\n    result = filter_jobs([fresh, stale], {\"max_age_days\": 1})\n    assert result == [fresh]\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_no_rules_returns_all():\n    jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i)) for i in range(3)]\n    assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — untested entirely, and the highest-risk gap\n\n`Store.diff` is the dedup source of truth; its new/changed/unchanged classification and the additive migration path are unverified.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id, title=title, url=\"u\", **kw)\n\ndef test_diff_first_seen_is_new(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n    assert store.count() == 1\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_job_reappears_in_neither_list(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])   # same content, second run\n    assert new == [] and changed == []\n\ndef test_diff_changed_content_hash_flags_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"Eng I\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Eng II\")])  # same key, different title -> different hash\n    assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\ndef test_diff_persists_across_store_instances(tmp_path):\n    path = tmp_path / \"persist.db\"\n    with Store(path) as s1:\n        s1.diff([_job()])\n    with Store(path) as s2:\n        new, _ = s2.diff([_job()])\n        assert new == []  # still known on reopen\n\ndef test_migrate_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_schema(tmp_path):\n    import sqlite3\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n            external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n            employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n            first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT NOT NULL);\n    \"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\ndef test_meta_get_set_roundtrip_and_upsert(store):\n    assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") is None\n    store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n    store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2024-02-01T00:00:00+00:00\")  # overwrite path\n    assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2024-02-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\ndef test_added_since_excludes_exact_timestamp_boundary(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n    assert store.added_since(ts) == []          # strictly-after semantics\n    assert len(store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")) == 1\n\ndef test_added_since_orders_by_first_seen_company_title(store):\n    store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"2\", title=\"Z Role\")])\n    store.diff([_job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"A Role\")])  # separate diff call -> later first_seen\n    rows = store.added_since(\"2000-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n    assert [r[\"title\"] for r in rows] == [\"Z Role\", \"A Role\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `fetchers.py` — largest gap: 15 parsers + retry/pagination logic, all untested\n\n**Missing error-handling tests** are concentrated here: `_request`'s retry/backoff, malformed payloads (missing required keys like `j[\"id\"]` which will raise `KeyError`), and `fetch_all`'s per-source failure isolation.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nfrom fetchers import (\n    parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby, parse_workday,\n    parse_google, _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_deshaw, parse_twosigma,\n    parse_optiver, parse_meta, parse_microsoft, parse_netflix, parse_amazon,\n    _amazon_posted_at, _request, fetch_source, fetch_all, FETCHERS,\n)\n\n# --- normalizer unit tests (one per ATS; showing representative subset) ---\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_maps_fields():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\",\n                       \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"}, \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}],\n                       \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n    jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n    assert jobs[0].location == \"NYC\" and jobs[0].department == \"Eng\"\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_empty_jobs_list():\n    assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_missing_jobs_key_raises_or_defaults():\n    assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {}) == []   # data.get(\"jobs\", [])\n\ndef test_lever_salary_formats_range_with_thousands_separator():\n    j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 120000, \"max\": 180000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n    assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 120,000–180,000\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_falls_back_to_description_when_no_range():\n    assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}) == \"Competitive\"\n\ndef test_lever_salary_no_data_returns_empty():\n    assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\ndef test_parse_ashby_skips_unlisted_jobs():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"isListed\": False}, {\"id\": \"2\", \"isListed\": True, \"title\": \"X\"}]}\n    assert [j.external_id for j in parse_ashby(\"c\", data)] == [\"2\"]\n\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_parses_us_date():\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"bad\", [\"\", \"garbage\", \"13/32/2024\", None])\ndef test_amazon_posted_at_malformed_returns_empty(bad):\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(bad) == \"\"\n\ndef test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_over_update_time():\n    job = [None]*20\n    job[12] = [1700000000, 0]  # create\n    job[13] = [1800000000, 0]  # update\n    ts = _ds1_posted_at(job)\n    assert \"2023\" in ts  # create-time year, not update-time\n\ndef test_ds1_posted_at_short_array_no_crash():\n    assert _ds1_posted_at([1, 2]) == \"\"\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_missing_blob_returns_empty_list():\n    assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty_list():\n    html = \"key: 'ds:1', ..., data:[not valid json, sideChannel\"\n    assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\ndef test_parse_deshaw_dedupes_repeated_job_ids():\n    page = 'data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">Eng</span>' * 2\n    assert len(parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)) == 1\n\ndef test_parse_twosigma_dedupes_triple_rendered_cards():\n    # regression test for the documented \"renders 3x\" layout quirk\n    ...\n\ndef test_parse_optiver_strips_join_us_jobs_prefix():\n    items = [{\"href\": \"/join-us/jobs/eng/nyc/swe\", \"title\": \"SWE\"}]\n    assert parse_optiver(\"optiver\", items)[0].external_id == \"eng/nyc/swe\"\n\ndef test_parse_meta_dedupes_by_id():\n    results = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\"}, {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A dup\"}]\n    assert len(parse_meta(\"meta\", results)) == 1\n\ndef test_parse_meta_skips_missing_id():\n    assert parse_meta(\"meta\", [{\"title\": \"no id\"}]) == []\n\n\n# --- retry wrapper (currently zero coverage of the backoff/error path) ---\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(respx_mock):\n    route = respx_mock.get(\"https://x.test/job\").mock(side_effect=[\n        httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True}),\n    ])\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x.test/job\", retries=2)\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and route.call_count == 2\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_exhausts_retries_raises_runtime_error(respx_mock):\n    respx_mock.get(\"https://x.test/job\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x.test/job\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_non_retryable_4xx_raises_immediately(respx_mock):\n    respx_mock.get(\"https://x.test/job\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(404))\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x.test/job\", retries=4)\n\n\n# --- fetch_source / fetch_all orchestration ---\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_value_error():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_per_source_failure(monkeypatch):\n    # one source raises, the other succeeds -> overall list still has the good jobs,\n    # and no exception propagates out of fetch_all\n    ...\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_respects_concurrency_semaphore():\n    # assert no more than N in-flight requests at once, using a counting mock transport\n    ...\n```\n\nAlso missing entirely: the **pagination loop termination conditions** for `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_workday`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_amazon` — each has slightly different \"stop when no fresh results\" / \"stop at `max_pages`\" / \"stop when `offset >= total`\" logic that's a prime source of infinite-loop or early-truncation bugs and currently has zero tests.\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_workday_stops_at_safety_cap_offset_5000(respx_mock):\n    # total never decreases -> loop must still terminate via the `offset > 5000` cap\n    ...\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_amazon_stops_when_page_returns_no_fresh_jobs(respx_mock):\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `pipeline.py` — untested entirely\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom pipeline import load_config, run\n\ndef test_load_config_applies_defaults(tmp_path):\n    p = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = load_config(p)\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8 and cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\ndef test_load_config_preserves_explicit_values(tmp_path):\n    p = tmp_path / \"cfg.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(\"sources: []\\ndb: custom.db\\nconcurrency: 3\\n\")\n    cfg = load_config(p)\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"custom.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_dry_run_does_not_persist_or_notify(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    # patch fetch_all to return canned jobs, assert Store file is untouched / not created,\n    # and dispatch() is never called\n    ...\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_normal_mode_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    # patch fetch_all + notify.dispatch, assert Store.diff was invoked and dispatch\n    # received the (new, changed) tuple from it\n    ...\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_returns_matched_new_changed_counts():\n    ...\n```\n\n**Integration test gap**: there's no end-to-end test that runs `run_sync()` against a real temp SQLite DB with a mocked HTTP layer and asserts the full new→changed→notified lifecycle across two consecutive runs (first run all-new, second run some-changed/some-unchanged). This is the single highest-value integration test missing, since it's the one path that exercises fetchers → filters → store → notify together.\n\n```python\ndef test_pipeline_end_to_end_two_runs(tmp_path, respx_mock, monkeypatch):\n    # respx_mock returns greenhouse fixture A on call 1, fixture B (one title changed,\n    # one job removed, one job added) on call 2. Assert run 1 -> all new; run 2 ->\n    # correct new/changed split and that removed job silently drops off the \"fresh\" list\n    # but isn't deleted from the DB (store never deletes).\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `notify.py` — untested entirely\n\nEvery notifier's env-var gating (the \"activate only when configured\" contract) is unverified, as is `dispatch`'s per-notifier exception isolation — a bug here would silently crash the whole run instead of just skipping a broken notifier.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom notify import (notify_console, notify_slack, notify_webhook, notify_email,\n                     notify_sms, _sms_body, dispatch)\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\", **kw)\n\ndef test_notify_console_no_jobs_prints_no_fresh(capsys):\n    notify_console([], [])\n    assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_webhook_url(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    notify_slack([_job()], [])   # must not raise / attempt network call\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_when_no_jobs_even_with_url(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n    notify_slack([], [])  # should short-circuit before httpx.post\n\ndef test_notify_slack_posts_when_configured(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"notify.httpx.post\", lambda url, **kw: calls.append((url, kw)))\n    notify_slack([_job()], [])\n    assert len(calls) == 1\n\ndef test_notify_sms_requires_all_four_twilio_vars(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)  # missing one var\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"notify.httpx.post\", lambda *a, **kw: calls.append(1) or (_ for _ in ()).throw(AssertionError(\"should not be called\")))\n    notify_sms([_job()], [])  # must no-op, not raise\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_and_reports_overflow_count():\n    jobs = [_job() for _ in range(10)]\n    body = _sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n    assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\ndef test_sms_body_is_ascii_only():\n    j = _job(title=\"Café Engineer\")  # non-ASCII char must not break GSM segment assumption\n    body = _sms_body([j], [])\n    # documents current behavior — does it strip/replace or pass through raw unicode?\n    ...\n\ndef test_notify_sms_raises_on_http_error(monkeypatch):\n    # resp.raise_for_status() should propagate — this is the one notifier meant\n    # to surface misconfig loudly rather than swallow it\n    ...\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_one_notifier_failure_from_others(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"broken webhook\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"notify.NOTIFIERS\", [boom, notify_console])\n    dispatch([_job()], [])\n    out = capsys.readouterr().out\n    assert \"notifier boom failed\" in out\n    assert \"NEW listing\" in out   # console notifier still ran despite prior failure\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` — untested entirely, and it's the most logic-dense module besides fetchers\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_new, cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, _chrome_bin\n\ndef test_db_mark_rejects_non_iso_watermark(capsys):\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\ndef test_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(capsys):\n    rc = cmd_db_mark([])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_db_mark_now_flag_sets_current_time(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    ...\n\ndef test_db_new_first_run_uses_since_days_window(tmp_path):\n    # no meta marker set yet -> since = now - since_days, first_run True\n    ...\n\ndef test_db_new_truncates_at_group_boundary_not_mid_group(tmp_path):\n    # two rows share identical first_seen (same pipeline run); with limit=1,\n    # the whole group must be kept together or excluded together, never split\n    ...\n\ndef test_db_new_watermark_only_advances_to_last_included_group(tmp_path):\n    ...\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_replaces_smart_quotes_and_em_dash():\n    html = \"<p>“Hello” — world</p>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert '\"Hello\" - world' in out\n    assert counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2 and counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_content_inside_style_and_script_tags():\n    html = \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1   # only the <p> occurrence counted, not the <style> one\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_does_not_mangle_tag_attributes():\n    html = '<a href=\"x&mdash;y\">\\u2014</a>'\n    out, _ = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'href=\"x&mdash;y\"' in out  # attribute text inside a tag must be untouched\n\ndef test_chrome_bin_prefers_chrome_path_env_when_it_exists(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    fake = tmp_path / \"chrome\"; fake.write_text(\"\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", str(fake))\n    assert _chrome_bin() == str(fake)\n\ndef test_chrome_bin_exits_when_nothing_found(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", raising=False)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"agent.shutil.which\", lambda name: None)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"agent.Path.exists\", lambda self: False)\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit, match=\"no Chrome/Chromium found\"):\n        _chrome_bin()\n\ndef test_pdf_render_missing_input_file_returns_2(tmp_path, capsys):\n    from agent import cmd_pdf_render\n    rc = cmd_pdf_render([str(tmp_path / \"missing.html\")])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_main_routes_db_new_db_mark_pdf_render_subcommands(monkeypatch):\n    # verify main() dispatches argv[0] correctly without invoking the real claude launcher\n    ...\n\ndef test_main_bare_invocation_is_interactive(monkeypatch):\n    # `agent.py` with no args -> interactive=True, mode_words=[]\n    ...\n\ndef test_main_mode_words_stop_at_first_flag(monkeypatch):\n    # `agent.py scan --foo bar` -> mode_words=[\"scan\"], extra=[\"--foo\",\"bar\"]\n    ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py` — thin wrapper, low priority but currently zero coverage\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\ndef test_cli_default_config_path(monkeypatch):\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"cli.run_sync\", lambda path, dry_run: calls.append((path, dry_run)))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\"])\n    from cli import main\n    main()\n    assert calls == [(\"sources.yaml\", False)]\n\ndef test_cli_dry_run_flag_passed_through(monkeypatch):\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"cli.run_sync\", lambda path, dry_run: calls.append(dry_run))\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\"])\n    from cli import main\n    main()\n    assert calls == [True]\n```\n\n---\n\n### Priority ranking\n\n1. **`store.py`** — dedup correctness is the whole point of the app; a silent bug here means duplicate notifications or missed jobs forever.\n2. **`fetchers.py` parsers + pagination loops** — 15 independent normalizers, several handcrafted regex scrapers (`deshaw`, `twosigma`, `google`); most likely to silently break when a site changes markup, and there's no regression net.\n3. **`filters.py`** — word-boundary/cutoff edge cases directly control what the user sees.\n4. **`pipeline.py` end-to-end test** — the only thing that would catch an integration break between fetch → filter → store → notify.\n5. **`notify.py`** — env-var gating and `dispatch` exception isolation.\n6. **`agent.py`** — `_normalize_ats` and the `db-new` group-boundary truncation logic are subtle enough to regress silently.\n7. **`cli.py`** — low risk, cheap to cover.\n",
